reviews.review_text: I really like zucchini you can use it in so many ways. The one way I use it is to shred it and put it in my beef meatloaf when I'm making it. It makes it so moist. It's so so great for zucchini bread and to serve just as a vegetable either steamedor sautéed with some onions. Very good.

reviews.title: Perfect size, fewer seeds
reviews.review_text: This was a great week for buying zucchini because normally the zucchini are so small. This time I got really good-sized beautiful ones. I'd say they were medium. Not the overgrown large ones with a ton of seeds. These have a lot of flesh and very few seeds. Great for cooking.

I don't know what variety the zucchini I got are but they are great! Not like the regular dark green kind, these are light green with white specs on them. They are almost buttery inside! Or maybe they are just young, I don't know about produce! But they are much better!

reviews.title: Freshest zucchini this season
reviews.review_text: Large zucchini are often shunned because they're overripe or hard. Not true here. This batch was super fresh and as firm as they should be in any size. I made zucchini bread and tendered 3 full cups from one shredded veggie which was all I needed. The price was great. Freshness was great. Neighbors loved the bread I shared with them too.

reviews.title: Delivery frees me from the store!
reviews.review_text: Having not seen the other zucchini available, I cannot tell if this was the best one possible, but it is quite acceptable. Not having to drive to the store, park, walk in and shop in person has opened up a new world for me. I will gladly continue to use the "delivery" option on the Wal-Mart app. I would like to suggest, though, a "comments" section with each order...e.g., "pick the greenest bananas". This IS provided by a local grocery app, so I know it is something which could be instituted.

reviews.title: I suggest only buying produce in the store !!
reviews.review_text: What i ordered was zucchini. what i got was large cucumbers. i keep having issues when i order online. Rotten 5 lb bage of potatoes. the person processing the order had to smell how bad they were but gave it to me anyway. Milk that should have been good for another week but was already bad and sour. Iceberg lettuce with green slimy leaves. just to mention a few. It was so convenient ordering online since i am disabled but now i don't trust that the produce will be good, so i have to shop in the store. my daughter usually picks up my order and brings it to me but she lives in st pete has elementary school kids that have to be pickeð up and she can't just turn around and bring the items back. Employees should be trained better or hire people who care. They need to understand that they are representing Walmart, and it looks bad on Walmart when they provide rotten groceries. They obviously dont take pride in their jobs.

reviews.title: EXTREMELY small - not what I needed at all.
reviews.review_text: This was the smallest zucchini I have ever gotten from Walmart - it's like the size of a whole dill pickle in a jar. This was meant for a specific recipe calling for a certain amount of veg, and this is about 1/3 of the amount I need. Pretty let down over this one. Y'all usually do a pretty decent job picking out produce, but this one was a fail. Now I've got to go out and see if I can find what I need from another store.

reviews.title: Poor produce selections
reviews.review_text: The zucchini was 7 inches long and looked like a mini cucumber. Fully developed zucchini are 11to 14 inches in length and an 3 inches in width . That was the expectation . Not what I received. Very poor produce choice. They should have been about 3/4 lb for one not less than a pound for two.

on Sept 24th I purchased 2 zucchini and 2 yellow squash . i could only use 1/2 of azucchini and 3/4 of a squash. very poor quality. I would not have purchased such meessed up vegetables . This was not the first time for bad choices by the person filling the order on vegatables

reviews.title: MOLDY ZUCCHINI!
reviews.review_text: I am disabled %26 can't get out to shop so I rely on services like the Walmart Plus program but am often discouraged %26/or frustrated with the quality assurance or lack there of. This time the zucchini was moldy when i went to use to make dinner %26 it was just 2 days after it arrived. I'm tired of calling %26 being told my feedback gets heard because nothing changes. I may just cancel my W-Plus membership %26 exclusively use door dash or instacart as their shoppers pay closer attention to providing quality products.

reviews.title: Walmart- do better!
reviews.review_text: Walmart- your curbside pick shoppers need to select better produce for your customers. This last order of zucchini was soft and moldy… I was in disbelief that it was hand selected by your own employee to fill my order. Walmart do better!!! When produce is selected online for curbside, give the best produce instead of what looks like you're ready to throw away. I threw it away… refund is due.

I've been trying your delivery for a while And although it's been great, I do have an issue that you charge for bags and then put one or two items in each bag. I wish you would load the bag the way I would if I was actually in the store, meaning several products can go in one bag.

It was a pickup order. I ordered 3 zucchini. Two were great and one was starting to spoil before I even got it. I don't like to give negative reviews. Good spirit of service would be if the shopper selected what they would want to select for themselves.

reviews.title: Not the best when delivered
reviews.review_text: Unfortunately, I have not had good experiences with zucchini that has been delivered. It is usually damaged and/or goes bad very quickly. One time they delivered a cucumber instead of a zucchini. I decided not to order very much “fresh produce” anymore because of that %26 some problems I've had with other fresh produce I've ordered before. Things go bad very fast %26 they don't appear to pick the produce carefully.

reviews.title: Excellent zucchini
reviews.review_text: The two zucchini I ordered were perfect. They weighed approximately 11 ounces each and cost one dollar each. Freshness was just right. I used them the next day to make two loaves of zucchini bread. Can't beat that. I was hesitant because of the number of one ratings but took a chance and it paid off. Maybe Walmart is paying attention and upping the quality. Thanks.

reviews.title: Zucchini bad shape

It's just the damage to the item… poor condition unbelievable that someone selected that today to be purchased w/drive up.

Had I been delivered a zucchini I'd be satisfied. However, I received a cucumber instead of a zucchini, a lime instead of a lemon, and green onions instead of asparagus. That teaches me for not wanting to go shopping in the rain and having groceries delivered. Excuse me while I go grab my raincoat and head out to ShopRite. 🤷‍♀️🤣

I suggest place each person's items in a box separate from another person's items so that the delivery person picks up the right box each delivery. The person giving the items for delivery needs to be more organized at Walmart.

reviews.title: Small issue
reviews.review_text: I love have my groceries delivered as I am 79 yrs old - this last time though who ever did the shopping put so many one item things in a single bag - I had so many bags - being that I have a bad back was hard putting everything away - if possible maybe not so many bags - I buy a month worth of groceries at a time each month

reviews.title: This is a cucumber
reviews.review_text: I wish walmart would offer an option to opt out of review requests but here we are. This is a cucumber. It's unspectacular. I don't usually order veg through the app because they're usually trash. But the cucumbers are usually consistently edible. Please stop asking me for reviews.

reviews.title: Best thing since sliced bread
reviews.review_text: My husband and I are up in age but the main reason we started getting our food delivered is because I broke my hip and several people told me about Walmart's delivery's. Best thing we ever did! We may continue after I'm able because we have to go up and down the isles looking for what we need, go thru checkout, bring the food home and drag it all in the house to put away! Of course we still have to put it away but it's brought to our door! Try it! You'll love it!

reviews.title: Small but good
reviews.review_text: It was a little bit on the small side, but it was fresh perfect for my bearded dragon not too crunchy not too soft. There were no bruising spots on it or anything it was. It was really good just a little on the small side, but for my bearded dragon, that was just fine.

reviews.title: Very helpful
reviews.review_text: I really appreciate it having my food delivered to my house. The drivers have all been very friendly and help me to put things in my buggy so I can take it onto my kitchen. I'm a very hard time walking and even even riding the carts around store, so this is really helped me.

reviews.title: Zucchini Shriveled %26 Old

To be fair Everything else in my order was great.

reviews.title: Annoyed shopper

reviews.title: Fresh off the vine zucchini.
reviews.review_text: I love zucchini and these were excellent. fresh, good sized with no blemishes. I only wished I'd ordered more. Squash are so versatile; steamed, fried, etc , and added to so many dishes. I like mine mixed with fresh corn and a little butter or olive oil....and they are healthy.

reviews.title: Good quality
reviews.review_text: They were vibrant, healthy, no damage and tasted great. I was NOT happy with the size, however. This has been consistently happening the last handful of times I ordered them now. I truly wish they were twice the size. So, if you want them for a recipe or even pan frying battered covered slices for more than yourself, make sure you order 1 per person, that is how small they are.

reviews.title: This isn't a vegetable. It's a lifestyle.
reviews.review_text: Let me tell you about this zucchini. Not just any zucchini. This… was THE zucchini. When I opened the Walmart bag, I wasn't prepared. There it was, shimmering under the kitchen light like it had descended directly from the Garden of Eden. I half expected a choir of angels to start humming. The firmness? Divine. The shade of green? A hue that can only be described as “photosynthesis chic.” I held it in my hand and whispered, “You complete me.” But here's the thing about zucchini: it's versatile. You can grill it, sauté it, spiralize it into noodles, or just stare at it longingly like I did for an uncomfortable amount of time before cooking it. I sliced it, and the sound was like the soft crunch of snow underfoot in a winter forest. Pure magic. When I finally ate it, I swear time slowed down. My taste buds signed a thank-you card. My ancestors applauded from beyond. Even my cat paused mid-nap to acknowledge the greatness that was unfolding. In short: this zucchini didn't just feed my body - it nourished my soul. If you're on the fence about buying a zucchini, let this be your sign. This isn't a vegetable. It's a lifestyle.

Received two cucumbers instead of my zucchini, first time it's happened ,usually the squash is very good so I will try one more time, but if it gets mixed up again I'll take my business elsewhere. Shoppers need training on the difference between a cucumber and a zucchini. Didn't realize the error till I got home I'll be checking better next time.

Chose 3 zucchini just the right size. Not to large. It was like I come them myself. I like the ones that are about 1 5 inches around and about 5 inches. They are tender, not too seedy. Great for slicing and sauteeing or like eating cucumber with a dip.

reviews.title: Almost garden fresh
reviews.review_text: Zucchini this day was firm and unblemished, perfect size for my cooking needs. The zucchini shipped to the store was of good quality and the associates were doing a nice job of keeping the display fresh.

reviews.title: Perfect Fresh Items

reviews.review_text: I purchased in June %26 July %26 the quality is great. They last a while in fridge. I cut them into spears, season w/ “Morton's Natures Seasoning.” Dry w paper towel if wet. Slice in half %26 use a peeler to sauté in pan %26 use for noodles w pasta sauce.

reviews.title: Absolutely disgusting!
reviews.review_text: The last 3 time I have purchased squash from Walmart it has ruined my food. I make large batches of soups and spaghetti and I freeze separate containers in my deep freezer for quick meals. I did not realize that for some reason the squash from here tastes extremely bitter as if it is not at all ripe even though it appears ripe. I could not figure out why my spaghetti has a bitter taste and then it happened again with my soup. I haven't been feeling well so I kept wondering if I had done something wrong or forgot something but I could not imagine what could have had this big impact. Yesterday I cut squash into spears and seasoned it and cooked it on it's own and when I ate it I immediately knew something was seriously wrong. I also immediately recognized it as the flavor I had been tasting in my spaghetti and soup. These batches of soups and spaghetti are made in huge stock pots and they usually cost $75-125 a batch. They usually last me 6 months or so. You can imagine how frustrating it is to be reminded every time I pull out a container for dinner. I am tempted to throw it all away and make a new batch but I am haunted by how much food will be wasted and the sheer cost all because the quality of the vegetables here is horrible.

I like these stewed for twice baked potato. I usually stuff them with meat filling and bake them for a healthy meal. The sky's the limit what you do with these.
